# Supabase usage (frontend)

## Keys

- Only `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` exist
  in this repo.
- **`SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is forbidden here.** If you think you need
  it, the operation belongs on DMIT, not the frontend.

## Clients

Use `@supabase/ssr`:

- `lib/supabase/client.ts` — browser client (Client Components).
- `lib/supabase/server.ts` — RSC / Server Action client (reads user cookies).
- `middleware.ts` — refresh the session cookie on every request.

All three use the **anon key**. The user's session (JWT in cookies)
authenticates RLS-protected reads.

## What to read directly via Supabase

Tables the user owns rows in, with RLS `auth.uid() = user_id`:

- `profiles` — name, plan, etc.
- `credit_ledger` — own ledger entries / balance view
- `usage_logs` — own usage rows
- `api_keys` — own keys (metadata only; never the raw secret, which DMIT
  shows once at creation time)

## What to NOT read/write via Supabase

- ❌ Don't write `credit_ledger` or `usage_logs` from the frontend, even if
  RLS allowed it. DMIT is the only writer.
- ❌ Don't `update` `profiles.plan` or any field that affects billing —
  call DMIT.
- ❌ Don't insert / delete `api_keys` from the frontend. Call DMIT's
  `/v1/keys` endpoints so the raw key is hashed with `TOKEN_PEPPER` server-side.
